## DATASET — brain_only/

### Overview
- **450 subjects** total on disk
- All subjects have T1 + brain mask
- Modality availability (all 450):
  - T1:     450 / 450 (100%)
  - T2-axi: 423 / 450 (94%)
  - FLAIR:  358 / 450 (80%)
  - T2-cor: 211 / 450 (47%)
  - mask:   450 / 450 (100%)

### Modality combination breakdown
- 200 subjects — T1 + T2-axi + FLAIR + mask
- 155 subjects — all 5 (T1 + T2-axi + T2-cor + FLAIR + mask)
-  42 subjects — T1 + T2-axi + T2-cor + mask
-  26 subjects — T1 + T2-axi + mask
-  14 subjects — T1 + T2-cor + mask
-  10 subjects — T1 + mask only
-   3 subjects — T1 + FLAIR + mask

### TWO POPULATIONS — identified via voting classifier

```python
def classify_acquisition(nifti_path):
    # Votes on 3 signals — 2-of-3 → "thick", else → "3d"
    thick_slice  = dz > 2.5
    anisotropy   = dz / ((dx + dy) / 2) > 2.0
    few_slices   = D < 60
```

**Population 1 — Thick-slice 2D (~38% of subjects)**
- dz = 4.8–7.2mm, anisotropy = 5–16
- 20–35 slices/volume, ~21 usable slices/subject
- Small in-plane: mostly 204×256 or 512×512
- Low empty rate: ~12% padding

**Population 2 — 3D Volumetric (~62% of subjects)**
- dz = 0.446–2.0mm, anisotropy = 0.54–2.05
- 120–560 slices/volume, ~209 usable slices/subject (after 1% fill filter)
- In-plane: 512×512, 256×256, 175×512, 155×288, etc. — highly heterogeneous
- High empty rate: ~43% average padding → **must crop before use**
- Includes "near-isotropic" 1.0–1.5mm subjects (correctly classified as 3D by voter)

### Key data quality findings
- **X4DSUZALBB**: fully empty T1 volume (100% empty slices) — must be dropped
- **IDPGHXRT4I**: 76.7% empty, tiny residual signal — borderline, flagged
- No corrupt files found otherwise
- 52 unique (H, W, dx, dy) spatial configurations — resampling required
- Most common shape: 512×512 @ 0.469mm (largest group)

### 2D Slice Inventory (100-subject sample, 1% fill threshold)
| Population | Subjects | Total slices | Usable | Empty % |
|------------|----------|-------------|--------|---------|
| 3D         | 62       | 23,372      | 12,961 | 42.8%   |
| Thick      | 38       | 936         | 814    | 12.4%   |

Extrapolated to all 450 subjects: **~55,000–65,000 usable 3D T1 slices**

